  <h1>
   string_width
  </h1>
  This function will return the width (in pixels) of the input string, taking into account any line-breaks the text may have. It is very handy for calculating distances between text elements based on the total width of the letters that make up the string
    as it would be drawn with
  <a href="../Drawing/Text/draw_text.htm">
   <span>
    draw_text()
   </span>
  </a>
  using the currently defined font.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">string_width(string);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      string
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        String
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The string to measure the width of.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var ww = string_width(str_Name + " "); draw_text(32, 32, str_Name)); draw_text(32 + ww, 32, "has won the game!");
</code></pre>
  The above code will get the width of the given string and then draw two lines of text, using the returned string width as a separator.
 </body>
